{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OVER Chris' shoulder, the sun sets and day becomes night.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 45 EXT. CAMPSITE, ORICK BEACH - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jan and Rainey on a blanket sharing a joint.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris lying beside the campfire in his sleeping bag.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jan takes a toke, passes the joint to Rainey.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: You know what Alex ought to do, Rainey?
{DIALOGUE}: He ought to come out to the Slabs this winter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 34.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RAINEY
{DIALOGUE}: Oh yeah.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rainey takes a toke on the joint.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RAINEY (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: You'd like that if you're still on the road.
{DIALOGUE}: Lot of fellow travelers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rainey offers the joint to Chris.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris passes it up with a hand gesture.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: What is that?
{DIALOGUE}: The Slabs?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RAINEY
{DIALOGUE}: It's down in Niland, California.
{DIALOGUE}: You know where the Salton Sea is?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: Near San Diego, yeah?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RAINEY
{DIALOGUE}: Well about 200 miles Northeast of there, but yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: Niland's off the east shore of Salton.
{DIALOGUE}: Wild place.
{DIALOGUE}: The navy bulldozed and abandoned a base there.
{DIALOGUE}: All that's left is a grid of concrete foundations.
{DIALOGUE}: They're scattered over about a square mile or so.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: When the weather turns cold across the rest of the country, people show up there by the thousands: snow birds...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RAINEY
{DIALOGUE}: Drifters...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Sundry vagabonds...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RAINEY / JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Like ourselves.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Livin' on the cheap under the sun.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: You sell your handcrafts there?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 35.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Oh yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: And a lot of second-hand goods.
{DIALOGUE}: There's a swap meet.
{DIALOGUE}: The people are cool.
{DIALOGUE}: There's even some kids running around sometimes.
{DIALOGUE}: Most everyone there, if they're not avoiding the cold, are at least dodging the IRS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RAINEY
{DIALOGUE}: Or the FBI.
{DIALOGUE}: CIA!
{DIALOGUE}: DDT!!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The three of them laugh.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: It's good.
{DIALOGUE}: You should check it out.
{DIALOGUE}: If you come, I'll make a proper hat for you.
{META_DATA}: (standing, shaking out her blanket)
