{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He watches Wayne below, as Wayne saunters out to the field to take a piss.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With his back to us, Wayne whips it out and starts pissing about 25 yards from the grain elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CU Wayne.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks up from his urination, the grain elevator behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see a slight mischievous smile come to his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He puts his hands up into the air when suddenly -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Six unmarked FBI vehicles surround him.
{META_DATA}: (Director's note: Triangulate three long lenses on Wayne as the mysterious cars enter each frame, as they skid to a dusty stop on all sides of him.)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris and the men of his crew look on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #1
{DIALOGUE}: I warned him about those little black boxes.
