{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARINE (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ...when I stumbled upon the book Chris had given me on his graduation day.
{DIALOGUE}: For some reason, it was the last line of the poem he read that really stuck out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FLASH BACK: (From page 2-3)
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 212 INT. DATSUN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris is holding a book from which he reads aloud the LAST LINE OF THE POEM...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: ...and I will tell about it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARINE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I asked Chris who had written the poem.
