{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 122.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARINE (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I realized that the words to my thoughts were of less and less meaning.
{DIALOGUE}: Chris was writing his story and it had to be Chris who would tell it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pictures in the scene BLUR as -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS (O.C.)
{META_DATA}: (in a far away, tunnel-like sound)
{DIALOGUE}: Mom, help me.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 213 INT. BEDROOM, MCCANDLESS HOME, ANNANDALE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Billie sitting bolt upright in the middle of the night, tears rolling down her cheeks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Walt awakens beside her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WALT
{DIALOGUE}: What is it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLIE
{DIALOGUE}: I wasn't dreaming!
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't imagine it!
{DIALOGUE}: I heard his voice, Walt.
{DIALOGUE}: I heard Chris.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Walt takes her in his arms, trying to squeeze life into both of them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CHAPTER 6: DELIVERANCE
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 214 FAIRBANKS ALASKA, SERIES OF STATIC IMAGES: Berms of cleared snow line the streets
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 1.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A GAS STATION (Gold Hill Gas and Liquor)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see Chris' writing appear on screen:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: APRIL 27, 1992
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 2.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OLD ALASKA PROSPECTOR'S STORE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WAYNE,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GREETINGS FROM FAIRBANKS!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THIS IS THE LAST TIME YOU SHALL HEAR FROM ME.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ARRIVED HERE TWO DAYS AGO.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 3.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SALOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 123.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 4.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A LIBRARY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IT WAS VERY DIFFICULT TO CATCH RIDES IN THE YUKON TERRITORY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 5.
